original: Björlander, Erik Artur, komminister, Grötlingbo, f. 24/3/10 i Mjölby av f. järnv:tj:m. Karl Emil Karlsson o. Josefina Johansson. G. 40 m. Nanna bisson. Barn: Gunnar f. 41. — Stud:-ex. v. Linköp. h. a. 1. 30, teol. fil. ex. v. Upps. univ. 33, teol. kand. där 38, prakt. teol. prov 38, prästex. i Visby 38, prästv. 38. Pastorsadj. i KHnte 38- 39, v. pastor i Othem 39-40, kommin. i Havdihems Näs, Grötlingbo o. Fide past. sed. 40. Ordf. i kyrkostämman i Grötlingbo o. Fide förs. sed. 40, ordf. i skolrådet i Grötlingbo sed. 44, kårchef f. Grötlingbo scoutkår sed. 41.
translated: Björlander, Erik Artur, a minister, Grötlingbo, born on March 24th, 1910 in Mjölby to railway conductor Karl Emil Karlsson and Josefina Johansson. Married in 1940 to Nanna Bisson with one child Gunnar born in 1941. He completed his secondary education in Linköping in 1930, a degree in theological philosophy at Uppsala University in 1933, a degree in theology in 1938, a practical theology exam in 1938, and ordained as a priest in Visby in 1938. He was a pastor's assistant in KHnte from 1938-39, an assisting pastor in Othem from 1939-40, and a minister in Havdihems Näs, Grötlingbo, and Fide from 1940 onwards. He was the chairman of the church council in Grötlingbo and Fide from 1940, chairman of the school council in Grötlingbo from 1944 and a scout leader for the Grötlingbo Scout Team since 1941.
